<paragraph blockId="57.[719,1314,2571,2998]" pageId="57" pageNumber="765">
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="765" type="discussion">Hylopetes siporawas described from an imma- ture specimen and was originally included in H. sagitta; an adult specimen is needed to clarify its taxonomic status. Monotypic.</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="765" type="distribution">Dimi Sipora I, Mentawi Is (off W umatra).</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
<subSubSection pageId="57" pageNumber="765" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="57.[719,1314,2571,2998]" lastBlockId="57.[110,1317,3005,3471]" pageId="57" pageNumber="765">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[721,997,2925,2958]" pageId="57" pageNumber="765">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body mean 140 mm, tail mean 160 mm; weight mean 89 g. The Sipora Flying Squirrel has dark brown forefeet and hindfeet. Ventral surface is buff to orange-buff, and there is white patch on chest. Tail is almost completely dull brownish black, paler at base, white at tip, and not markedly bicolored.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
